author: Julie Bykowicz, Associated Press
title: IRS complaint filed over Rubio-boosting secret-donor group
text: Photo: Rick Bowmer, AP Republican presidential candidate Marco Rubio speaks during a campaign rally at the Utah State Fairpark Monday, Oct. 19, 2015, in Salt Lake City. Republican presidential candidate Marco Rubio speaks during a... WASHINGTON (AP) — A Washington watchdog group filed a complaint Tuesday with the IRS about a secret-donor nonprofit organization that is spending millions of dollars on commercials to boost Marco Rubio's 2016 prospects.
